\begin_layout Plain Layout
Entanglement may be regarded as one of the main characteristics distinguishing
 quantum from classical mechanics.
 Entanglement involves quantum correlations such that the measurement outcomes
 in one subsystem are related to the measurement outcomes in another one.
 Within the standard framework, given a quantum system composed of 
\begin_inset Formula $n$
\end_inset

